OL,3,CPrince Harry reflects on mother's
OL,4,Clegacy as he walks in Ukraine minefield
OL,6,FThe prince was also taken to the
OL,7,Fmemorial in the town of Bucha, where
OL,8,Fthey remember the atrocities which
OL,9,Fwere inflicted on the people living
OL,10,Fhere during the month in which Russia
OL,11,Foccupied the area.
OL,13,FSt Andrew's Church is the site of a
OL,14,Fmass grave where 119 of the victims
OL,15,Fwere buried in March 2022.
OL,17,FInside, during a private meeting, the
OL,18,Fprince was shown a display of graphic
OL,19,Fphotographs that were taken after the
OL,20,FRussian soldiers had left.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1777104370
OL,3,CPrince Harry reflects on mother's
OL,4,Clegacy as he walks in Ukraine minefield
OL,6,FThey show the bodies of the civilians
OL,7,Fwho were murdered and executed in
OL,8,FBucha, which is now widely recognised
OL,9,Fas a war crime.
OL,11,FIt's estimated 500 Ukrainian men,
OL,12,Fwomen and children were killed in that
OL,13,Fone month under occupation - many of
OL,14,Fthe bodies were set alight in an
OL,15,Fattempt by the Russians to cover up
OL,16,Ftheir crimes.
OL,18,FIt is a sobering experience to see the
OL,19,Fphotographs and to imagine the horror
OL,20,Fof what happened here.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
